{"id":19668,"date":"2024-01-02T23:47:01","date_gmt":"2024-01-03T07:47:01","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/?p=19668"},"modified":"2024-01-17T20:07:43","modified_gmt":"2024-01-18T04:07:43","slug":"morning-mountain","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2024\/01\/02\/morning-mountain\/","title":{"rendered":"MORNING MOUNTAIN"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><em>Less than ten minutes from Nelson, the network of trails here go through cedar forests and wildflowers. Morning Mountain operated as a ski hill until 1999 when the lodge burned down. The mountain biking trails climb all the way up to Toad Mountain.<\/em><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Difficulty:<\/strong> B1 moderate <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Distance: <\/strong>9 km round trip<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Elevation:<\/strong>\u00a0+544m<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Time:<\/strong> 4-5 hours<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Season:<\/strong>\u00a0late April to early November<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Drive. <\/strong>From Nelson, head west on Highway 3A and turn left on Granite Road just as you leave town. Drive 4.1km and turn left on\u00a0Blewett Ski Hill Road \u2013 2WD low-clearance Park.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Use the Trail Forks app.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Trail<\/strong>. There is a choice of trails to ascend but Bottoms Up and Upper Bottoms are the easy green trails. Avoid the black diamond trails.<br \/>\n<\/span><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">1. Bottoms Up trail, reach a junction in 2km and switch to the green Upper Bottoms trail to gain the top of the network in about 2 hours with the best viewpoint in 10 minutes. Gold larches in September.<br \/>\n<\/span><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Continue on Upper Bottoms and turn left on Giveout Creek Road for 0.3km, turn right on the signed \u2018Bedframe\u2019 trail, and walk down Bedframe for just 0.1km and the best viewpoint.<br \/>\n<\/span><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong><em>Return<\/em><\/strong> to Upper Bottoms on a choice of trails avoiding the ones that end on Granite Road.<br \/>\n2. Silverking side. P<\/span><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">ark on Giveout Creek FSR (room for 3 vehicles, 4WD HC). Walk up Fairly High to Very High, then down Upper Highballer and Highballer to the viewpoint on Bedframe and back along Fairly High. All forested trails <\/span><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">A\/B1. Distance:14 kilometres. Elevation gain: 450 meters. Time: <\/span><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">5 &#8211; 6 hours.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><strong>Reference.<\/strong> https:\/\/westkootenayhiking.ca\/?s=MORNING+MOUNTAIN+<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Less than ten minutes from Nelson, the network of trails here go through cedar forests and wildflowers. Morning Mountain operated as a ski hill until 1999 when the lodge burned down. The mountain biking trails climb all the way up &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2024\/01\/02\/morning-mountain\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"jetpack_post_was_ever_published":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_access":"","_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs":false,"_jetpack_